      <h1 class='title'>Armed Forces' Pay Review Body</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 cc59-60WS</cite>
      
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_59ws' title='Col. 59WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c59WS' name='column_59ws' href='#column_59ws' rel='bookmark'>59WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-04910'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_13'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-william-bach' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_13' title='Link to this speech by Mr William Bach' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-william-bach" title="Mr William Bach">Lord Bach</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0669P0-04910">My right honourable friend the Secretary of State for Defence (Mr Geoffrey Hoon) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04911">The 2005 report of the Armed Forces' Pay Review Body has been published today. Copies of the report are available in the Vote Office and the Library of the House. I wish to express my thanks to the chairman and members of the review body for their clear and wide-ranging report.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04912">The AFPRB has recommended an increase in basic military salary of 3 per cent for all other ranks and officers. the AFPRB has also recommended increases in the rates of specialist pay (e.g. flying pay, submarine pay, diving pay and hydrographic pay), and in accommodation charges. The AFPRB also recommended a five per cent increase to rates of longer separated service allowance and longer service at sea bonus which are designed to compensate for separation.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04913">
          <table>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
