          <td>Total</td>
          <td>272,362</td>
          <td>16,424</td>
          <td>288,786</td>
          </tr>
          </table>
          </p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04916"><span class="italic">Resource DEL</span></p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04917">The change in the resource element of the DEL of &#x00A3;423,701,000 arises from a &#x00A3; 101,530,000 increase in the voted element of the resource DEL and an increase of &#x00A3;322,171,000 in the non-voted element of the resource DEL mainly to the department's non-departmental public bodies.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04918"><span class="italic">Voted Resource DEL</span></p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04919">The &#x00A3;101,530,000 increase in the voted element of the resource DEL arises from a &#x00A3;171,074,000 increase in
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_60ws' title='Col. 60WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c60WS' name='column_60ws' href='#column_60ws' rel='bookmark'>60WS</a>
          The additional cost to the defence budget will be &#x00A3;216 million. This will be met within existing departmental expenditure limits.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04920">The AFPRB's recommendations are to be accepted in full, with implementation effective from 1 April 2005.</p>
        </blockquote>
